  "query": "What is the comparative effectiveness of deploying acoustic devices on fishing gear, vessels, or moorings for reducing human-wildlife conflict at wild fisheries?",
  "relevant_summary": "Across action documents, evidence on human\u2013wildlife conflict outcomes shows: (1) Acoustic devices on fishing gear: five of six studies (including controlled and before\u2013after designs) reported reduced damage to fish catches and/or nets by dolphins and seals, while one study found no reduction in swordfish catch damage by California sea lions [2808]. (2) Acoustic devices on vessels: one randomized, controlled study reported no reduction in predation of squid catches by Risso\u2019s dolphins when devices of two types were used [2815]. (3) Acoustic devices on moorings: one randomized, controlled study reported a reduction in the number of harbour seals feeding on migrating juvenile salmon [2816].",
